.TH "IMAGEBUILDER-PUT-IMAGE-RECIPE-POLICY" "a" "" ""
.SH NAME
imagebuilder-put-image-recipe-policy \- Applies a policy to an image recipe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Applies a policy to an image recipe. We recommend that you call the RAM API \fI\%CreateResourceShare\fP to share resources. If you call the Image Builder API \fBPutImageRecipePolicy\fP , you must also call the RAM API \fI\%PromoteResourceShareCreatedFromPolicy\fP in order for the resource to be visible to all principals with whom the resource is shared.
.sp
See also: AWS API Documentation
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
  put\-image\-recipe\-policy
\-\-image\-recipe\-arn <value>
\-\-policy <value>
[\-\-cli\-input\-json | \-\-cli\-input\-yaml]
[\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton <value>]
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH OPTIONS
.sp
\fB\-\-image\-recipe\-arn\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the image recipe that this policy should be applied to.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-policy\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The policy to apply.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP | \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP (string)
Reads arguments from the JSON string provided. The JSON string follows the format provided by \fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP\&. If other arguments are provided on the command line, those values will override the JSON\-provided values. It is not possible to pass arbitrary binary values using a JSON\-provided value as the string will be taken literally. This may not be specified along with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&.
.sp
\fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP (string)
Prints a JSON skeleton to standard output without sending an API request. If provided with no value or the value \fBinput\fP, prints a sample input JSON that can be used as an argument for \fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP\&. Similarly, if provided \fByaml\-input\fP it will print a sample input YAML that can be used with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&. If provided with the value \fBoutput\fP, it validates the command inputs and returns a sample output JSON for that command.
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
.SH EXAMPLES
.sp
\fBTo apply a resource policy to an image recipe\fP
.sp
The following \fBput\-image\-recipe\-policy\fP command applies a resource policy to an image recipe to enable cross\-account sharing of image recipes. We recommend that you use the RAM CLI command \fBcreate\-resource\-share\fP\&. If you use the EC2 Image Builder CLI command \fBput\-image\-recipe\-policy\fP, you must also use the RAM CLI command \fBpromote\-resource\-share\-create\-from\-policy\fP in order for the resource to be visible to all principals with whom the resource is shared.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
aws imagebuilder put\-image\-recipe\-policy \e
    \-\-image\-recipe\-arn arn:aws:imagebuilder:us\-west\-2:123456789012:image\-recipe/example\-image\-recipe/2019.12.02/1 \e
    \-\-policy \(aq{ "Version": "2012\-10\-17", "Statement": [ { "Effect": "Allow", "Principal": { "AWS": [ "123456789012" ] }, "Action": [ "imagebuilder:GetImageRecipe", "imagebuilder:ListImageRecipes" ], "Resource": [ "arn:aws:imagebuilder:us\-west\-2:123456789012:image\-recipe/example\-image\-recipe/2019.12.02/1" ] } ] }\(aq
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
